HEADWORD: Thulium
<hw>Thu"li*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Thule</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare metallic element
of the lanthanide group having atomic number 69, and atomic weight
168.93. It is found in the mineral gadolinite and other minerals,
together with other rare earths.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

